{"id":26298457115,"name":"Test","node_id":"WFR_kwLOA_1uaM8AAAAGH4KcGw","head_branch":"fix/workflow-permissions-hardening","head_sha":"a8ecaa7d1dd78cde6078b89f9129630cfe6876f6","path":".github/workflows/run-tests.yml","run_number":53542,"run_attempt":1,"event":"pull_request","display_title":"chore(ci): add explicit `permissions:` blocks to all workflows","status":"completed","conclusion":"success","workflow_id":10954,"check_suite_id":70351148367,"check_suite_node_id":"CS_kwDOA_1uaM8AAAAQYUFVTw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26298457115","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26298457115","pull_requests":[{"id":3731475000,"number":23977,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/pulls/23977","head":{"ref":"fix/workflow-permissions-hardening","sha":"a8ecaa7d1dd78cde6078b89f9129630cfe6876f6","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}},"base":{"ref":"master","sha":"575ba916870b86f483b99ba5af5959b08868bef0","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}}}],"created_at":"2026-05-22T16:03:54Z","updated_at":"2026-05-22T16:20:09Z","run_started_at":"2026-05-22T16:03:54Z","jobs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26298457115/jobs","logs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26298457115/logs","check_suite_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/check-suites/70351148367","artifacts_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26298457115/artifacts","cancel_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26298457115/cancel","rerun_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26298457115/rerun","head_commit":{"message":"chore(ci): add explicit `permissions:` blocks to all workflows\n\nHardens workflows against supply-chain attacks (e.g. the Megalodon\ncampaign that hit 5,561 GitHub repos on 2026-05-18) by declaring the\nminimum GITHUB_TOKEN scope each workflow needs, instead of inheriting\nthe repo-level default.\n\nBefore this PR, 13 of 16 workflows had no `permissions:` block and\ninherited the repo default. A compromised third-party action would\nhave run with that default scope. With explicit blocks, each workflow\nis locked to least-privilege.\n\nPer-file scopes:\n\n- contents: read (the 11 read-only ones):\n    analyse-pr.yml, check-formatting.yml, generate-merge-boms.yml,\n    performance-tests-compare.yml, performance-tests-scheduled.yml,\n    performance-tests.yml, run-api-analytics-tests-clickhouse.yml,\n    run-api-analytics-tests-doris.yml, run-api-analytics-tests.yml,\n    run-api-tests.yml, run-tests.yml\n\n- deploy-instance.yml: contents: read, checks: read,\n    pull-requests: write (wait-on-check-action + maintain-one-comment)\n\n- destroy-instance.yml: contents: read, pull-requests: write,\n    issues: read (maintain-one-comment delete + gh api issues events)\n\nPairs with planned repo-settings change:\n  Settings → Actions → General → \"Workflow permissions\"\n    → switch default from \"Read and write\" to \"Read repository\n       contents and packages\"\n    → uncheck \"Allow GitHub Actions to create and approve pull\n       requests\"\n\nAfter this PR is merged the repo default flip becomes safe because\nevery workflow declares its own scope; the default no longer matters\nfor code paths.\n\nExpect some 403 \"Resource not accessible by integration\" errors on\nthe first runs after the repo default is flipped — each is a workflow\njob needing a per-job scope addition. The 3 scopes above are best-\nguess from a static read of each workflow; CI failures will surface\nany missed scope.\n\nAI Assisted","author":{"name":"Morten Svanaes","email":"msvanaes@dhis2.org"},"id":"a8ecaa7d1dd78cde6078b89f9129630cfe6876f6","tree_id":"68938dfe21c3e2e2e025dba6c49e71e8a79af9d4","timestamp":"2026-05-22T16:03:00Z","committer":{"name":"Morten Svanaes